tiv erscheinen. Als eine vielversprechende Variante entwickelt Jochen Dallmer das Modell eines aufgeklärten Hedonismus, welcher das Streben nach subjektivem Wohlbefinden zu einem Beitrag für Nachhaltigkeit werden lässt.  afunded by transcript: Open Library 2020 (Politik)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBildung. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aGlück. 4aGlücksforschung. 4aHedonismus. 4aKonsum. 4aMaterialismus. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPostwachstum. 4aSuffizienz. 4aUmweltpolitik. 4aWohlbefinden. 4aWohlstand. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh  aCivil Society.  aConsumption.  aEducation.  aEducational Research.  aEnvironmental Policy.  aHappiness Research.  aHappiness.  aHedonism.  aMaterialism.  aPhilosophy.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aPost-growth.  aProsperity.  aSufficiently.  aWell-being.2 atranscript: Open Library 2020 (Politik)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2020z9783111025124oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383765247540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839452479?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839452479zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/do